New Records: Rassie van der Dussen scored a brilliant century and formed a double-century partnership with Quinton de Kock, earning him Player of the Match
Key Match Events: South Africa won the match by 190 runs
Phillips got to 60 runs before being dismissed
New Zealand lost three wickets in a row after a strong start
Post-Match Reflections: Tom Latham, New Zealand captain, expressed no regrets about winning the toss despite the loss
Miscellaneous Highlights: New Zealand dropped to fourth place with a heavy net run rate defeat
South Africa moved to the top of the standings
